	Lohan comedy    
	 New York, Dec. 28 (PTI): Actress Lindsay Lohans rise to fame and her subsequent fall because of drug and alcohol related problems in Hollywood has inspired a comedy called Dogs in Pocketbooks.       
	Model and heiress Lydia Hearst Shaw, 26, will portray a character based on Lohan, the New York Post reported.       
	Lydia will play a bratty movie goddess in and out of rehab, in trouble with the law, and hounded by greedy agents, predatory paparazzi, off-the-wall stalkers and crazed media  a role obviously based on Lindsay Lohan, screenwriter Charles Casillo said.                                                                                                                                                       
